a) Improved safety: it is safer to store and transport the feedstock material (powder sheets) and there are no add-on requirements to the MAPS process and system for metal powder handling;   
b)Higher efficiency for printing MMS:the inter-material change time during MAPS is only several minutes,as opposed to the long-pause time such as tens of hours for switching materials in SLM;   
c) Cost reduction: no feedstock surrounding the components to be built is needed and,thus,fewer volumes of feedstock materials are required for building.In this way,a minimum amount of material wastage is produced;   
d) Easy to operate and shorter clean-up time between fabrications: a few minutes are enough to clean the chamber after the MAPS printing.Such a task is increasingly labour-intensive for regular SLM practices.
